history.content:
Hello,

I am a new L&S CS intended transfer student for this Fall 2021, and I wanted to get some advice on what classes I should enroll in for this upcoming semester. Ideally, I would prefer a lighter schedule during my first semester so that I can adjust both to the Cal CS rigor and the big transition to campus. 

Note: I have completed a CS61A articulation in community college, and I do not have a Math 54 articulation. I also plan on staying the extra semester to graduate (5 semesters in total).

My plan is to definitely take CS61B, and ee16a this Fall, but I wanted to get some further advice on the third class. Right now, I am thinking of taking Data 8 because the Data Science major would likely be my backup.

What are your thoughts on me taking CS61B, ee16a, and Data8 in my first semester (all for a letter grade)? Or please let me know if you have any other suggestions for the third class.

I would really appreciate any advice or feedback you can offer me.
